 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uluterinshadowstalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LuterinShadowstalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/21/02 8:53:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4479.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Glowing Orb of Luclinite</span><hr size=1> It could still be that you needed one orb for each mini quest to get a link.<br>
<br>
And they just drop in alot of places since each person who wants to get a key needs 10 orbs totally, and you wouldn't be able to do more than 1 link quest at a time either.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukanamdar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kanamdar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/22/02 9:12:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4479.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Glowing Orb of Luclinite</span><hr size=1> The main bottleneck for the Veeshan Peak quest was the Trakanon Kill. Everything else was moderately easy, but you had to prove you were of the required skill/level by going to a Trak raid.<br>
<br>
And there was a bottleneck, to avoid everybody and their friend to get a VP key, and having 4 raids trying to get into VP at the same time.<br>
<br>
So, the orb is either a bottleneck, or it isn't. If it is, too many orbs drop per &quot;raid period&quot; for it to be used only once, so it makes sense that multiple orbs would be required. And then, it makes sense for the orb to be used once for each link: it makes impossible for someone to rush a &quot;long, involved quest&quot;: you need to be at at least ten Luclin raids, with a break between each raid to complete the rest of the quest leg. Which means that, no matter how much you're playing, the quest will take at least half a month to complete. Even if you have priority at each raid you attend for the Luclin globe, and the rest of each step is doable without a raid-sized force.<br>
<br>
If it isn't, then it doesn't make sense for so many of these orbs to drop either. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umojak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mojak</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/22/02 9:34:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4479.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Glowing Orb of Luclinite</span><hr size=1> we've gotten several of them, have some ideas what they are used for<br>
